<TITLE> Asian U-14 tennis begins Wednesday in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 10 (bdnews24.com)  The Prime Bank Under-14 Asian Tennis Tournament, organised by the Bangladesh Tennis Federation (BTF) and financed by Australian Open Authority, begins Wednesday at the National Tennis Complex in Ramna with seven nations taking part in the meet. With a view to developing tennis in Asia, the Australian Open Authority is financing different Asian countries to organise the tournament for some years. "With the financial support from the Australian Open, the Asian Tennis Federation (ATF) will organise a total of 40 tournaments in different countries round the year," BTF general secretary Sanaul Haq said at a press conference at his office Monday. Eight boys and as many girls will be qualified for a one-month follow- up training in Australia after the year-round U-14 tournaments in Asia, added Haq. A total of 32 boys and 21 girls will compete in the final round of the tournament. India, Malaysia, Japan, Sri Lanka, Myanmar, Vietnam, Pakistan and hosts Bangladesh are participating in the tournament. Youth and Sports Adviser Tapan Chowdhury will open the tournament while Prime Bank Limited chairman Ajam J Chowdhury will be present as special guest. Managing director of sponsor Prime Bank Shahjahan Bhuiyan, BTF treasurer Manjurur Rahman Raskin and tournament director Sahin were present among others on the occasion. 
